3P7.F.summary: Pandora A/S designs, manufactures, and markets hand-finished and contemporary jewelry worldwide. The company's jewelry material includes silver and gold, man-made stones, gemstones, cultured pearls, and diamonds, as well as enamel, glass, leather, and textile products. Its products primarily include charms, bracelets, rings, earrings, necklaces, and pendants. The company operates through a network of 2,690 concept stores, which include 1,382 company owned stores and 1308 partner owned stores; and 4,402 other points of sale, as well as eSTOREs. Pandora A/S was founded in 1982 and is headquartered in Copenhagen, Denmark.
